 Block-Sharded RMS Norm — Design Plan

  Math

  For each row vector x of length W:
  y = x * rsqrt(sum(x²) / W + ε)

  Block Sharding & The Cross-Core Problem

           Core(0,0)       Core(0,1)       Core(0,2)
          ┌───────────┬───────────┬───────────┐
  Row 0   │ shard_W   │ shard_W   │ shard_W   │  ← same tensor rows, W split across 3 cores
          │ tiles     │ tiles     │ tiles     │
          ├───────────┼───────────┼───────────┤
  Row 1   │           │           │           │  ← different tensor rows (independent)
          └───────────┴───────────┴───────────┘

  - Core grid: R rows × C columns
  - Each core's shard: [shard_H_tiles, shard_W_tiles]
  - Cores in the same grid row hold adjacent W-slices of the same tensor rows → they must communicate to compute the full-row sum of squares
  - Grid rows are independent — no communication needed between them

  Algorithm (per tile-row of the shard)

  ┌───────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────┐
  │ Phase │                                    What                                     │             Where             │     Communication      │
  ├───────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────┤
  │ 1     │ Read shard_W_tiles input tiles from local shard                             │ Reader → cb_input             │ None                   │
  ├───────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────┤
  │ 2     │ Square each tile, reduce_row → 1 partial-sum tile                           │ Compute                       │ None                   │
  ├───────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────┤
  │ 3     │ All-gather: each core multicasts its partial to all C peers in the grid row │ Writer (send) / Reader (recv) │ Multicast + semaphores │
  ├───────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────┤
  │ 4     │ Sum C partials → multiply by 1/W → add ε → rsqrt → inv_rms (column vector)  │ Compute                       │ None                   │
  ├───────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────┤
  │ 5     │ Re-read input tiles, multiply each by inv_rms → output                      │ Reader + Compute              │ None                   │
  ├───────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────┤
  │ 6     │ Write output tiles to output shard                                          │ Writer                        │ None                   │
  └───────┴─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┴───────────────────────────────┴────────────────────────┘

  Multicast Strategy (Phase 3)

  All-to-all within each grid row:

  1. Each core writes its partial-sum tile to a unique slot (offset core_col * tile_size) in cb_remote_partials on every peer core using noc_async_write_multicast
  2. After writing, each core does noc_semaphore_inc on every peer to signal arrival
  3. Each core waits for semaphore == C-1 (all peers have written)
  4. Write own partial to its own slot locally (no NoC needed)
  5. Compute sums all C slots

  This allows all cores to multicast simultaneously — no sequential round-robin.

