  Critical sizing: cb_sq must hold shard_W_tiles because square and reduce_row are sequential compute helpers — the reduce can't start consuming until all squares are produced.

  Kernel Roles

  Reader (BRISC, NoC0):
  - Pre-loads 1/W scaler tile into cb_scaler
  - Per tile-row: reads shard_W_tiles from local shard → cb_input
  - Receives multicast partials from peers (semaphore wait)
  - Re-reads input tiles for Phase 5

  Compute (TRISC):
  - Phase 1: mul_tiles (square) → cb_sq, then reduce<SUM, ROW> → cb_partial
  - Phase 3: Sum C partials from cb_remote_partials, multiply by scaler, add ε, rsqrt_tile → cb_inv_rms
  - Phase 4: mul_tiles_bcast_cols(cb_input, cb_inv_rms) → cb_output

  Writer (T6, NoC1):
  - Per tile-row: waits for cb_partial, multicasts to all peers in grid row
  - Increments semaphore on peers after multicast
  - Writes cb_output tiles to output shard

